task.summary: Default task
I have the modular configuration, time functions and user functions working
Updating the progress. Building a previous work-day routine.
Got the get_previous_work_day to work
Got the get_previous_work_day to work
I got some of the rudimentary signals working. I have a ways to go to recall exactly how a UI like this works, with all the back and forth.
Added a base shotgun collect library
Added a base shotgun collect library, got the Graphic UI started, and made progress with the time sheets and clocks
Made significant progress in building the UI over the weekend. Time for a good commit.
Going to put a hold on this for now, and start working on engine logic for a while.
Got the UI time creator to create a new time sheet.
I have more of the UI done, some of the time stuff figured out. Basically, too many unfinished changes to make note of. WIP.
Added and updated elements
Long weekend. I need to make changes for which having a backup will be beneficial.
Got the last settings or time sheets to show up auto-selected.
I have the button switches working and some of the bugs worked out of the start and stop time stuff. Still very early.
Added some graphic elements
Fixed some button state elements.

Through some ham-fisted bullshittery the clock in and clock out system is functioning. There are lots of holes and things that probably will not work they way it is setup now. But... that will get fixed.
Found a few new hurdles to overcome. Have some of the messaging systems starting to work.
Fixed a bug (I think) in the Task drop down. And got some basic stuff working for the runtime counter
I have to rework how I'm sharing the timesheet between stuff.
Got the main running time counter to work. Found a flaw in the Switch system. It runs the clock with the last timesheet even if it doesn't create a timesheet

Got the clock running error fixed, but discovered another bug-issue. The Task list is still not properly updating with all of the tasks. JazzBand project - Casino asset has 10 tasks. None were listed. Have to find out why.
Fixed an issue with the switch not running the clock
Got the timer and the Upper monitor to work.
Got a lot of new things done in the UI and system. Still can't get the drop downs to be clean. Nonetheless, the basic in and out system is working.
Back that ass up
I'm trying to make the date counters REALLY dynamic, but it's not working. I'm going to a more hard-wired approach just to make it work, but I wanted to save a copy of this before I revert.
Got the date rollers working. Last major functional bit is the clocks. Then there's the pop-ups for setting the dates manually, and fixing the drop-downs
I figured out how to GET the dials to all rotate, now I just have to get that to actually work in the system.
Got the clocks to work, although there is some minor translational crap going on, and the images get a little aliasy while running. Not really a problem for now.
Added duration to the clock-out procedure
Still have to figure out the meter dials, but for the most part it is working.
I found an irritating bug with the tasks setup. They don't work right. Also, Switching with error-checks still clocks you out, instead of just rejecting the button push.
Fixed the task menu issue
The solution to the tasks list has arisen a new bug. I'm using this commit to find differences.
